# API Endpoints

The ECG monitoring system exposes the following API endpoints:

## Data Retrieval

- [web/api/get_ecg_data.php](mdc:web/api/get_ecg_data.php): Retrieves ECG data for a specific configuration
  - GET request with `config_id` parameter
  - Returns time-series ECG data for visualization

- [web/api/get_diagnostic.php](mdc:web/api/get_diagnostic.php): Retrieves diagnostic information
  - GET request with `id` parameter
  - Returns diagnostic details and measurements

## Data Storage

- [web/api/save_config.php](mdc:web/api/save_config.php): Saves patient configuration information
  - POST request with patient details and acquisition parameters
  - Handles data encryption and security

- [web/api/save_ecg.php](mdc:web/api/save_ecg.php): Stores ECG signal data
  - POST request with ECG values and timestamps
  - Links data to a specific acquisition configuration

